<h2 data-start="5432" data-end="5451"><strong>How to Reach?</strong></h2>
<ul data-start="5453" data-end="5731">
 	<li data-start="5453" data-end="5498">
<p data-start="5455" data-end="5498"><strong data-start="5455" data-end="5467">By Train</strong>: Reach Haridwar or Rishikesh</p>
</li>
 	<li data-start="5499" data-end="5576">
<p data-start="5501" data-end="5576"><strong data-start="5501" data-end="5512">By Road</strong>: Take a shared taxi/bus to Govindghat (275 km from Rishikesh)</p>
</li>
 	<li data-start="5577" data-end="5731">
<p data-start="5579" data-end="5594"><strong data-start="5579" data-end="5593">Trek Route</strong>:</p>

<ul data-start="5597" data-end="5731">
 	<li data-start="5597" data-end="5639">
<p data-start="5599" data-end="5639">Govindghat → Pulna (4 km) – By vehicle</p>
</li>
 	<li data-start="5642" data-end="5680">
<p data-start="5644" data-end="5680">Pulna → Ghangaria (9 km) – On foot</p>
</li>
 	<li data-start="5683" data-end="5731">
<p data-start="5685" data-end="5731">Ghangaria → Valley of Flowers (4 km) – On foot</p>
</li>
</ul>
</li>
</ul>
<h2 data-start="5738" data-end="5784"><strong>A Humble Request – Respect the Mountains</strong></h2>
<p data-start="5786" data-end="5882">At <em data-start="5789" data-end="5807">Himalayan Hikers</em>, we follow and promote <strong data-start="5831" data-end="5856">eco-friendly trekking</strong>. We urge all visitors to:</p>

<ul data-start="5884" data-end="6035">
 	<li data-start="5884" data-end="5901">
<p data-start="5886" data-end="5901">Avoid plastic</p>
</li>
 	<li data-start="5902" data-end="5943">
<p data-start="5904" data-end="5943">Don’t pluck flowers or disturb plants</p>
</li>
 	<li data-start="5944" data-end="5974">
<p data-start="5946" data-end="5974">Maintain silence and peace</p>
</li>
 	<li data-start="5975" data-end="6011">
<p data-start="5977" data-end="6011">Respect local guides and porters</p>
</li>
 	<li data-start="6012" data-end="6035">
<p data-start="6014" data-end="6035">Bring back your waste</p>
</li>
</ul>
<h2 data-start="6042" data-end="6079"><strong>Final Words: Now It’s Your Turn</strong></h2>
<p data-start="6081" data-end="6277"><strong data-start="6081" data-end="6123">The <a href="https://www.himalayanhikers.in/hurry-up-valley-of-flowers-trek-open/">Valley is open</a>. Nature is calling.</strong><br data-start="6123" data-end="6126">Come once — and rediscover yourself. This is more than a trek. It is a spiritual retreat. Join Himalayan Hikers and be part of something unforgettable.</p></p>

                                  
                              </p>
